# ---------------------------------------------------------
# CONTENT GOVERNANCE (MANDATORY - NEVER BREAK)
# ---------------------------------------------------------

## âŒ STRICTLY FORBIDDEN

### 1. Real Client/Company Names
- NO real client names without written permission
- NO identifiable project names
- Use: "a manufacturing company", "e-commerce platform"

### 2. Numbers & Metrics (ALL NUMBERS FORBIDDEN)
- NO client counts ("500+ clients")
- NO years of experience ("Since 2000")
- NO team size ("100+ employees")
- NO metrics/percentages ("40% improvement")
- NO pricing/currency ("$50", "â‚¹10,000")
- Use: "many clients", "experienced provider", "extensive portfolio"

### 3. Emojis (ZERO TOLERANCE)
- NO emojis in ANY visible content
- NO: ðŸš€ âœ¨ ðŸ’¡ â­ ðŸŽ¯ or ANY emoji character
- Use: Professional SVG icons from Heroicons only

### 4. Certification & Compliance Claims
- NO: ISO, SOC, HIPAA, PCI, GDPR, DPDPA certifications
- NO: "Certified", "Compliant", "Standards"
- NO: Regulatory claims or badges
- Use: "Industry best practices", "Professional standards"

### 5. Outcome-Based Case Studies
- NO client names in case studies
- NO specific outcomes/results
- NO before/after comparisons
- NO ROI or performance metrics
- Use: Process-focused descriptions, technology approach

### 6. Superlatives & Marketing Hype
- NO: "Best", "#1", "Leading", "World-class"
- NO: "Award-winning" without actual awards
- NO: Empty marketing fluff
- Use: "Experienced", "Professional", "Trusted"

### 7. Numbered Visual Elements
- NO numbered badges (01, 02, 03...)
- NO letters as design elements (A, B, C...)
- Use: Meaningful SVG icons only


# ---------------------------------------------------------
# REQUIRED FEATURES (MUST IMPLEMENT)
# ---------------------------------------------------------

## âœ… Technical Requirements

### 1. Mobile-First Responsive
- Test on: 375px (mobile), 768px (tablet), 1280px (desktop)
- Use Tailwind: text-base md:text-lg lg:text-xl pattern
- Touch targets minimum 44x44px

### 2. Accessibility (WCAG AA)
- Skip to main content link (required)
- ARIA labels on interactive elements
- Semantic HTML (header, main, nav, footer)
- Keyboard navigation functional
- Color contrast ratio > 4.5:1
- Focus indicators visible

### 3. SEO Metadata (Every Page)
- Title tag (50-60 characters)
- Meta description (150-160 characters)
- Canonical URL
- Open Graph tags
- Proper heading hierarchy (H1 â†’ H2 â†’ H3)

### 4. Schema Markup (Approved Types Only)
âœ… ALLOWED:
- Organization (generic info only)
- WebPage (basic page info)
- Service (NO ratings/awards)
- BreadcrumbList (navigation)

âŒ FORBIDDEN:
- AggregateRating
- Review
- Award
- Certification
- Any metrics (employee count, years, etc.)

### 5. Design System
- Create lib/design-tokens.ts FIRST
- Define colors, typography, spacing
- Use consistently across all components
- Icons: Heroicons (SVG, 2px stroke) only


# ---------------------------------------------------------
# AI ASSISTANT BEHAVIOR
# ---------------------------------------------------------

## When User Requests Forbidden Content:

**STOP and respond with:**
```
âš ï¸ CONTENT VIOLATION DETECTED

Requested: [what user asked for]
Issue: [why it's forbidden]

Approved Alternatives:
A) [option 1]
B) [option 2]
C) [option 3]

Please select an option or provide guidance.
```

## CTA/Button Changes:

**NEVER auto-fix buttons. Always:**
1. Document current behavior
2. List 2-3 fix options
3. Wait for explicit approval

## Content Creation:

**Before generating ANY content:**
- Verify: No client names, numbers, emojis, certifications
- Use: Neutral, professional, non-promissory language
- Focus: Capabilities and process, not outcomes

## Code Generation:

**Always include:**
- Metadata (title, description, canonical)
- Schema markup (approved types only)
- Accessibility features (skip link, ARIA)
- Mobile-first responsive classes
- Design tokens from lib/design-tokens.ts


# ---------------------------------------------------------
# EXECUTION MODES
# ---------------------------------------------------------

## MODE: NEW_PROJECT
When starting new project:
1. Reference: @DEVELOPMENT-GUIDE.md
2. Create design-tokens.ts FIRST
3. Setup layout with schema markup
4. Stop after each file for review
5. Enforce all content rules

## MODE: CONTENT_AUDIT
When auditing existing content:
1. Scan for ALL forbidden patterns
2. Generate report with page locations
3. Recommend 3 alternatives per issue
4. DO NOT auto-fix
5. Wait for approval

## MODE: NEW_PAGE
When creating new pages:
1. Show content outline FIRST
2. Get approval before full implementation
3. Include metadata, schema, accessibility
4. Test mobile responsiveness
5. Verify no violations


